Are you sure we want to use std::optional? When I was working on unpackProperties for bool it didn't really matter but for more complicated types like, string, vector bmcweb binary was bigger.

Personally I prefer optionals, but if smaller binary size is priority we should use pointers like it was used before. To be consistent we should use pointer for all optional properties.

We can't use ptr in this case for passwordExpired, because it needs to be able to be set on line 1396, which requires an object that can have ownership.  I did make this change for remoteUser though.
